# Cap blender's parallelism (see env/low-mem). blender's Cycles kernels need
# ~4 GiB per compile job — far above the global ~2 GiB/job budget — and it
# OOM-killed the build at -j(global) (run 26892007888 died at 905/927). Only
# blender is capped here; other heavy packages (browsers, qtwebengine, etc.)
# build at the global resource-aware MAKEOPTS, which is sized to the runner's
# RAM, so they don't need a per-package cap on an adequately-sized builder.
media-gfx/blender        low-mem
